Welcome back to The Best & The Brightest. I=E2=80=99m Tara
Palmeri, writing to you from Los Angeles, where I=E2=80=99ll be appearing o=
n Real Time With Bill Maher tomorrow night trying to explain the past three=
 years=E2=80=94I mean weeks=E2=80=94of Trump=E2=80=99s presidency. It=E2=80=
=99s been a tour de force: Greenland, Panama, the Gulf of America, Gaz-a-La=
go, USAID, the NCAA, government buyouts, Iran=E2=80=A6 what=E2=80=99s next?=
 Lots of window-smashing and noise, but uncertain results.

=C2=A0

In tonight=E2=80=99s issue, my candid conversation with Senator John Fetter=
man, who=E2=80=99s trying to thread the needle with Trump=E2=80=94attemptin=
g the delicate political choreography of knowing when to fight back versus =
when to let the president=E2=80=99s self-created chaos collapse on its own.=
 In this interview, the senior senator from Pennsylvania offered surprising=
