ouse to really run the
table.

=C2=A0

I=E2=80=99d be surprised if they don=E2=80=99t move to kill the filibuster,=
 because the Democrats, including myself, ran on eliminating the filibuster=
=2E If you drop the filibuster in the S=
enate, then you can pass anything, bec=
ause they=E2=80=99ll have all the votes they need to do that. That=E2=80=99=
s really the last emergency brake on the legislative freedom to remake soci=
ety.

The DOGE Black Box
------------------

What do you think about Elon Musk=E2=80=99s expansive role? No one
elected him and yet he seems to have more power than you, a sitting senator=
=2E I know the Democrats are suing DOGE,=
 but it just feels a little too late.

=C2=A0

It=E2=80=99s not clear. There=E2=80=99s an agenda there, and I don=E2=80=99=
t agree with it, and I think a lot of it=E2=80=99s strange. Who knows what=
=E2=80=99s happening right now? But Musk was empowered by a president who w=
as empowered by the American people, who said, =E2=80=9CWe want things
shaken up.=E2=80=9D At least half the population agrees with what=E2=80=99s=
 happening.

=C2=A0

We lost, I think, in part because we were perceived as the party of chaos. =
The second the Republican side becomes the chaos party, things will shift a=
nd people will realize, =E2=80=9CI voted against this kind of chaos. I want=
 more stability.=E2=80=9D There will be a moment when a critical mass of pe=
ople decide the Republicans are
becoming the party of chaos. For now, we knew that it was going to be a sto=
rm, but there=E2=80=99s a lot more snow on the ground than anyone would hav=
e predicted. But you have to keep your shovel and figure out where you=E2=
=80=99re going to respond, and push back. But if you keep yelling, people a=
re going to stop paying attention. Democrats have already used the most sev=
ere kinds of language and condemnation. It=E2=80=99s going to lose its valu=
e and no one=E2=80=99s going to pay attention to it.

=C2=A0

You seem to be saying that Americans only have a chance to rebuke Trump at =
the ballot box in 2026.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

I=E2=80=99m worried about 2026, but actually I=E2=80=99m concerned about th=
e next crazy thing that comes out of the chute. If they really affect the p=
eople, like going after the Department of Education, I will weigh in on thi=
ngs, the
things that really matter.

=C2=A0

Could you make it through a Democratic primary for president?

For anyone on the Democratic side who=E2=80=99s angry at me for having dinn=
er with Trump, or trying to fight for wins, I=E2=80=99d like to remind you =
that I=E2=80=99m the senior senator in Pennsylvania, and I am in the same p=
arty as you. I am
never rejecting my party. I haven=E2=80=99t changed my values. I=E2=80=99ve=
 just chosen to have a different approach. And I=E2=80=99d like to remind e=
veryone that our next president won=E2=80=99t be determined by the votes in=
 Oregon or California or in Connecticut or these deep blue states. It will =
be determined in states like mine. We=E2=80=99re on the top of that list, a=
nd everyone has to remember how we almost lost our seats in Michigan and in=
 Wisconsin and Nevada. We easily could have been 56-44 in the Senate.

So
if you=E2=80=99re angry with me for talking with the Republicans, I think y=
ou have to remember the way the race worked out, and that the states that r=
eally determine who=E2=80=99s going to be the next president are going to b=
e those six or seven states. And remember that the things we say, or that w=
e=E2=80=99re forced to defend, are going to get weaponized, with unlimited =
money. And that=E2=80=99s exactly what happened to the vice president in 20=
24.

